<div class="row featurette">
  <div class="col-md-12">
    <p>
    Most online mind mapping tools first focused on mapping capabilities, then
    built collaboration on top of that. We did that with the main MindMup app two years ago as well. The result was clunky and severely
    limited. Almost any good online mind mapping tool today offers concurrent editing, 
    but the conversation part is far below what modern users expect.
    Chat systems are non existing or severely limited, comments are not preserved well, there is no way to see
    collaborators faces or talk to them directly while mind mapping. For effective collaboration,
    groups had to set up a separate video or audio channel using Skype or
    Hangouts. Synchronising participants across two different channels, setting
    up resource permissions and managing presence was headache. Many teams use mind maps as an overview of their project, and 
    attempting to review another project document, for example disucssing a presentation
    or reviewinf a spreadsheet, required a third collaboration channel to be opened and synchronised with the first two. It was a hassle,
    interrupting discussions just when people want to get creative. No more! 
    </p>
    <p>Likewise remote video conferencing tools aren't that good for visualising ideas. People often
    start talking online about something that seems simple at first, but then wished for a nice whiteboard to visualise
    the connections in their minds. This required interruption to set up a separate document in a different tool. Coordinating
    invitations and privilege lists disrupts conversations just when they become interesting. No more! 
    </p>
    <p>Instead of building collaboration on top of a mind
    mapping tool, we built mind mapping inside a great collaboration tool. MindMup for Google Hangouts runs a mind mapping session in the same
    window as a video conference. It works out of the box, without the need to coordinate multiple collaboration channels or participant lists. All Hangout participants
    immediately get access to the mind maps, and they can collaborate instantly.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>



