<div class="row featurette">
  <div class="col-md-12">
    <h2>Brainstorm and review ideas visually, using video and audio conversations</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <p>
    MindMup for Hangouts runs as an optional pane inside the Hangout application, so you can collaborate on a mind map and talk
    to other participants at the same time, even look at their faces. Everyone in the hangout is looking at the same mindmap, so 
    concurrent updates across the globe are instantly visible to your collaborators, using Google's Hangout infrastructure. There is no need
    to set up any other software or coordinate different tools for mapping and audio chats.
    </p>
    <p>
    Of course, great collaboration needs more than just concurrent updates. To really benefit from a group mind-mapping session, people
    need to know what everyone else is thinking as well. With MindMup for Hangouts, we're coming as close to a physical presence as possible,
    by allowing you to hear and see collaborators, but also enssuring that you know what everyone else is doing around the map.
    </p>    
    <p>
    As people are moving around the map, you can see their profile photos move and follow their thoughts. When your colleagues
    add new ideas or update map nodes, you'll get a quick overview with pop-up speech bubbles. This ambiental information makes
    groupwork much more powerful than just remote simultaneous document editing. 
    <p>
    <p>
    A map stays associated with the hangout, so you can leave at any time and come back, and your ideas will wait for you.
    </p>    
  </div>
